✅ Problem 1: Thread-Safe Banking Application

### ✔️ Clean Code

```java
class BankAccount {
    private double balance;
    private volatile boolean isLocked = false;

    public BankAccount(double initialBalance) {
        this.balance = initialBalance;
    }

    public synchronized void updateBalance(double amount) {
        if (!isLocked) {
            balance += amount;
            System.out.println("Balance updated. New balance: " + balance);
        } else {
            System.out.println("Transaction failed: System is locked.");
        }
    }

    public void triggerLockdown() {
        isLocked = true;
        System.out.println("System is now in lockdown!");
    }

    public double getBalance() {
        return balance;
    }
}
```

### 🔍 Key Idea (Exam er jonno)

* `synchronized` → একসাথে একটাই thread balance change করতে পারবে (race condition বন্ধ)
* `volatile` → `isLocked` সব thread real-time update দেখবে (cache issue হবে না)

👉 Short line:
**Thread safety = synchronized + volatile**

